iving them aid and comfort . No person shall be convicted of treason unless on the testimony of two witnesses to the same overt act , or on confession in open court . The Congress shall have power to declare the punishment of treason , but no attainder of treason shall work corruption of blood , or forfeiture except during the life of the person attainted .	0
