arty , the Supreme Court shall have original jurisdiction . In all the other cases before mentioned , the Supreme Court shall have appellate jurisdiction , both as to law and fact , with such exceptions , and under such regulations as the Congress shall make . The trial of all crimes , except in cases of impeachment , shall be by jury ; and such trial shall be held in the state where the said crimes shall have been committed ; but when not committed within any state , the trial shall be at such place or places as the Congress may by law have directed . Treason against the United States , shall consist only in levying war against them , or in adhering to their enemies , giving them aid and comfort . No person shall be convicted of treason unless on the testimony of two witnesses to the same overt act , or on confession in open court . The Congress shall have power to declare the punishment of treason , but no attainder of treason shall work corruption of blood , or forfeiture except during the life of the person attainted .	0
