d to their consideration such measures as he shall judge necessary and expedient ; he may , on extraordinary occasions , convene both Houses , or either of them , and in case of disagreement between them , with respect to the time of adjournment , he may adjourn them to such time as he shall think proper ; he shall receive ambassadors and other public ministers ; he shall take care that the laws be faithfully executed , and shall commission all the officers of the United States .	0
