ich shall be made in pursuance thereof ; and all treaties made , or which shall be made , under the authority of the United States , shall be the supreme law of the land ; and the judges in every state shall be bound thereby , anything in the Constitution or laws of any State to the contrary notwithstanding . The Senators and Representatives before mentioned , and the members of the several state legislatures , and all executive and judicial officers , both of the United States and of the several states , shall be bound by oath or affirmation , to support this Constitution ; but no religious test shall ever be required as a qualification to any office or public trust under the United States .	0
